This is libsie 1.1.6, a library for reading SIE files.

BUILDING
========

To build the library on Unix, do the usual:

    $ ./configure
    $ make

libapr is required to be installed, and apr-1-config must be present
in the default path.

For Windows, a Visual Studio 2013 solution file (sie.sln) is in the
windows directory.  A compiled version of libapr must be installed
in the external directory as follows:

[libsie source root]/external/include/apr*.h
[libsie source root]/external/lib/libapr-1.dll
[libsie source root]/external/lib/libapr-1.lib
[libsie source root]/external/lib/x64/libapr-1.dll
[libsie source root]/external/lib/x64/libapr-1.lib

USAGE
=====

The best way to learn to use libsie initially is to take a look at the
libsie-demo.c file, which lives in the src/libsie-demo directory.
This is both a working SIE file dumper and a verbose tutorial into
basic libsie usage.

A documentation package specific to using libsie with HBM SoMat
products is available at the HBM SoMat Resource Center at
http://www.hbm.com/somat/resource_center.html.  (Free registration
required.)

The reference documentation for libsie is included in the sie.h header
file, and also rendered into HTML in the docs/reference directory as
libsie-reference.html.

A document describing the SIE file standard, including the theory and
basic structure of SIE data, as well as documents describing the
'core' and 'somat' data and metadata schemas, are in 'docs/standard'.
In particular, read up to and including the section on "The SIE Data
Model" in the standard.

FEEDBACK
========

If you'd like to make suggestions, report a bug, or help to improve
libsie, please send mail to support@usa.hbm.com.

